        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14569",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assigning to Matthew.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-12T12:23:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-12T12:23:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14573",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just to give feedback, if this is mandatory indeed (I found and read the [spec|http:\/\/www.xmlrpc.com\/spec] in the meantime and it's not so clear on this) this may be a week implementation in the Java-based XML-RPC service I have to query.  What would be your advice then?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-12T13:00:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-12T13:00:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14652",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you give an example fault response payload that triggers the exception? Zend_XmlRpc_Fault::loadXml() only throws exceptions for the following conditions:\n\n* malformed XML\n* malformed fault response, which means that it doesn't minimally have <fault><value><struct><\/struct><\/value><\/fault> structure\n* BOTH code AND message missing from the fault struct\n\nIn the case of a missing code, it simply sets it to '404', and uses the message provided. My inclination is that the response you're getting back is so far different from a typical XML-RPC response as to be unrecognizable. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-17T11:03:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-17T11:03:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14719",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Apologies for the delay - this is what I get when I dump:\n\n{code}\n$httpResponse = $http->request(Zend_Http_Client::POST);\n{code}\n\nResponse:\n\n{code}\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<methodResponse>\n<fault>\n<value>\n<struct>\n<member>\n<name>faultString<\/name>\n<value>java.lang.ClassCastException: java.lang.Integer<\/value>\n<\/member>\n<member>\n<name>faultCode<\/name>\n<value><int>0<\/int><\/value>\n<\/member>\n<\/struct>\n<\/value>\n<\/fault>\n<\/methodResponse>\n{code}\n\n\nException:\nFault code and string required",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T06:51:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T06:51:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14722",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is with the XML, in particular, the faultString value; it's missing the tag indicating the value type. Instead of:\n{code}\n<value>java.lang.ClassCastException: java.lang.Integer<\/value>\n{code}\nit should be reading:\n{code}\n<value><string>java.lang.ClassCastException: java.lang.Integer<\/string><\/value>\n{code}\n\nThe only way to fix this is to intercept the XML as it arrives and insert the tag (can be done using either regexp, DOM, or SimpleXML).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T07:55:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T07:55:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14723",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fault response returned from third-party server does not conform to XML-RPC spec; not an issue of ZF.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T07:56:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T07:56:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14830",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The XML-RPC spec states that if no type supplied, \"string\" is assumed. So this fault is not so far away from the standard. ;-)\n\nhttp:\/\/www.xmlrpc.com\/spec\nhttps:\/\/issues.apache.org\/jira\/browse\/XMLRPC-142?page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#action_12499656",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-29T05:52:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-29T05:52:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15162",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_XmlRpc_Value is correctly defaulting to using strings if no type is provided; however, Zend_XmlRpc_Fault is not using Zend_XmlRpc_Value to pull the fault struct.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-13T09:21:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-13T09:21:09.000+0000"
                },
